  "description": "Chitra Bahadur K.C. (born 2 February 1941) is a Nepalese politician, former deputy prime minister, and minister of poverty alleviation. He is the current chairman of the Rastriya Janamorcha. He has been elected to the Pratinidhi Sabha multiple times, representing the Baglung district. Originally a member of the Communist Party of Nepal (Fourth Convention), he later joined the Communist Party of Nepal (Masal). K.C. is widely known for his staunch opposition to federalism in Nepal, particularly on the basis of ethnic identity.",
